# Incident Report 004 – User Account Monitoring

## Incident Summary

Wazuh detected multiple user account management events including account creation, account modification, group membership changes, and account deletion.

---

## Objective

To verify Wazuh's ability to monitor Windows account management activities.

---

## Alerts Observed

- User account enabled or created
- User account changed
- User account disabled or deleted
- Users Group Changed
- Administrators Group Changed

---

## Investigation

Windows generated account management events whenever user accounts were modified.

Wazuh collected these logs and generated corresponding security alerts.

Monitoring these events is essential for detecting privilege escalation or unauthorized account creation.

---

## MITRE ATT&CK

T1136 – Create Account

T1098 – Account Manipulation

---

## Security Impact

Unauthorized account creation may indicate:

- Persistence
- Insider threats
- Privilege escalation

---

## Recommendations

- Monitor administrator account creation.
- Review group membership changes.
- Audit account lifecycle regularly.

---

## Outcome

Successfully validated user account monitoring using Wazuh.
